## Goal

Complete ADR-0016 observational-memory behavior end-to-end: coverage accounting, gap-aware compaction/catch-up, append-only pruning/tombstones, audit recall, CLI/MCP/server surfaces, and runtime adapter docs/stubs.

## Boundaries

- Do **not** edit ADR files unless explicitly asked.
- Preserve privacy filtering before writes and append-first ordering before SQLite projection updates.
- Observation records remain session-continuity projections, not durable claim triples.
- Keep tests deterministic/offline; no live Pi/Claude/Codex/OpenCode integration.
- Runtime adapters should be boundary/stub/docs only, not real editor/agent plugins.

## Non-goals

- Building LLM-based observers.
- Adding public REST endpoints beyond existing MCP/OAuth server.
- Changing durable claim recall semantics.
- Deleting historical observation data.

## Slice Order

1. Core observation coverage + uncovered-gap summary warnings.
2. Append-only prune/tombstone model + replay/audit visibility.
3. Catch-up observer/draft flow + compaction/pruning blockers.
4. Trigger-decision reasons for uncovered gaps.
5. CLI surfaces.
6. MCP/server tool surfaces and scopes.
7. Runtime adapter stubs/docs.
8. README/how-it-works updates and full verification.

## Plan

1. Add core tests first in `crates/aver-core/tests/observational_memory.rs` covering:
   - coverage counts `event_ids`, `covered_event_ids`, `uncovered_event_ids`, and ratio/count fields;
   - compaction summary includes an uncovered-gap warning;
   - catch-up drafts close gaps before checked compaction;
   - pruning appends tombstones instead of deleting;
   - ordinary list/summary/recall hide pruned observations;
   - explicit audit recall/list includes pruned observations;
   - replay rebuilds pruned state from JSONL;
   - `should_extract_memories_detailed` includes `UncoveredObservationGap`.

2. Extend `crates/aver-core/src/types.rs`:
   - add `Observation.pruned_at: Option<i64>` and `Observation.prune_reason: Option<String>`;
   - extend `ObservationCoverage` with `event_count`, `covered_count`, `uncovered_count`, `coverage_ratio`, `has_gaps`;
   - add `ObservationVisibility::{Active, Audit}`;
   - add `ObservationPruneMarker` or equivalent view struct if useful;
   - add `ExtractionTriggerReason::UncoveredObservationGap`.

3. Add migration `migrations/0011_observation_pruning.sql`:
   - `ALTER TABLE observations ADD COLUMN pruned_at INTEGER;`
   - `ALTER TABLE observations ADD COLUMN prune_reason TEXT;`
   - add index for active observations, e.g. `(session_id, pruned_at, ts)`.
   - Ensure migration prefix is next contiguous after current `0010_vector_index.sql`.

4. Modify observation core logic in `crates/aver-core/src/lib.rs`:
   - replace `INSERT OR REPLACE INTO observations` with idempotent insert/duplicate validation;
   - if a deterministic observation id already exists but is pruned, create a new active suffixed id rather than unpruning old data;
   - make `list_observations_for_session` return only active observations;
   - add `list_observations_for_session_audit`;
   - make `get_observation` ordinary/active-only or add `get_observation_with_visibility`;
   - make `recall_observation` active-only;
   - add `recall_observation_audit`.

5. Implement coverage APIs in `crates/aver-core/src/lib.rs`:
   - keep `observation_coverage(session_id)` as active coverage;
   - add `observation_coverage_with_visibility(session_id, ObservationVisibility)`;
   - compute coverage only from source event ids belonging to that session;
   - expose stable uncovered ids sorted by event id.

6. Implement gap warnings and blockers in `crates/aver-core/src/lib.rs`:
   - update `assemble_compaction_summary` to include a clear warning section when active coverage has uncovered gaps;
   - add `assemble_compaction_summary_checked(session_id)` that returns `Error::UncoveredObservationGap { session_id, uncovered_event_ids }`;
   - add the new error variant in the `Error` enum;
   - use checked summary for automatic compaction paths.

7. Implement catch-up flow in `crates/aver-core/src/lib.rs`:
   - add `catch_up_observations_from_observer(session_id, observer)` that passes only uncovered events to the observer;
   - add `catch_up_observations_from_drafts(session_id, drafts)` for CLI/MCP surfaces;
   - validate each draft’s `source_event_ids` belongs to the session and intersects uncovered ids;
   - return recorded ids plus before/after coverage.

8. Replace destructive pruning in `Store::prune_observations`:
   - before pruning, refuse if current active coverage has gaps;
   - simulate candidate pruning and refuse if it would create uncovered gaps;
   - append JSONL tombstone entries with `kind: "prune_observation"` before SQLite updates;
   - update rows with `pruned_at` and `prune_reason` instead of `DELETE`;
   - do not expose pruned observations to ordinary list/summary/recall.

9. Update replay in `crates/aver-core/src/lib.rs`:
   - extend `ReplayReport` with `observation_prunes`;
   - handle `kind: "prune_observation"` in `apply_log_line`;
   - apply tombstones idempotently after `record_observation`;
   - preserve audit recall after replay.

10. Update extraction trigger decisions:
    - modify core `should_extract_memories` internals or add `should_extract_memories_detailed`;
    - include `ExtractionTriggerReason::UncoveredObservationGap` whenever coverage has gaps;
    - keep the existing bool API as a compatibility wrapper over detailed decisions.

11. Add CLI surfaces in `crates/aver-cli/src/main.rs`:
    - `list-observations --session-id <id> [--audit]`;
    - `observation-coverage --session-id <id> [--audit]`;
    - `catch-up-observations --session-id <id> --drafts-jsonl <path|->`;
    - `prune-observations --session-id <id> --keep <n> --reason <text>`;
    - extend `recall-observation --id <id> --audit`;
    - extend `compaction-summary --session-id <id> [--catch-up-drafts-jsonl <path|->] [--allow-uncovered]`.
    - Add CLI integration tests in `crates/aver-cli/tests/observational_memory_cli.rs`.

12. Add server/MCP surfaces in `crates/aver-server/src/tools.rs`:
    - params/views for coverage, list observations, catch-up, prune, audit recall, and richer compaction summary;
    - update `ShouldExtractMemoriesView` to include `reasons: Vec<String>` while preserving `should_extract`;
    - ensure errors surface blocker reasons clearly.

13. Wire MCP tools in `crates/aver-server/src/mcp.rs`:
    - add tools `observation_coverage`, `list_observations`, `catch_up_observations`, `prune_observations`;
    - update `recall_observation` and `assemble_compaction_summary` params;
    - update server instructions string.

14. Update scopes in `crates/aver-server/src/scopes.rs`:
    - read scope: `observation_coverage`, `list_observations`, `recall_observation`, `assemble_compaction_summary`;
    - write scope: `record_observation`, `catch_up_observations`, `prune_observations`;
    - update `ALL_TOOL_NAMES` and tests.

15. Add runtime adapter stubs:
    - create `crates/aver-core/src/runtime_adapters.rs`;
    - export from `crates/aver-core/src/lib.rs`;
    - define enum/metadata for `Pi`, `ClaudeCode`, `CodexOpenAi`, `OpenCode`, `Mcp`, `GenericJsonlCli`;
    - document each adapter’s event source, observer boundary, compaction hook, and audit recall capability;
    - keep as pure metadata/stubs, no external process execution.

16. Update docs:
    - `README.md`: add implemented ADR-0016 surfaces, CLI examples, MCP tool list, prune/audit semantics.
    - `doc/how-it-works.md`: update runtime flow and implementation status for observation coverage, catch-up, blockers, tombstones.
    - create `doc/runtime-adapters.md`: Pi, Claude Code, Codex/OpenAI coding agents, OpenCode, MCP, generic JSONL/CLI harness contracts.
    - Do not edit `doc/adr/*`.

17. Verification:
    - `cargo fmt --all`
    - `cargo clippy --workspace --no-deps -- -D warnings`
    - `cargo test --workspace --locked`
    - optionally `just check` if time allows.

## Files to Modify

- `crates/aver-core/src/types.rs` — observation visibility/prune fields, coverage fields, trigger reason.
- `crates/aver-core/src/lib.rs` — coverage, catch-up, checked summary, tombstone pruning, replay, errors.
- `crates/aver-core/src/validation.rs` — prune reason / visibility validation if needed.
- `crates/aver-core/src/lib.rs` exports — add runtime adapter module.
- `crates/aver-cli/src/main.rs` — new/extended commands.
- `crates/aver-server/src/tools.rs` — params/views/tool implementations.
- `crates/aver-server/src/mcp.rs` — MCP wrappers and instructions.
- `crates/aver-server/src/scopes.rs` — scope mapping and tool list.
- `README.md` — user-facing behavior/status.
- `doc/how-it-works.md` — architecture/status update.

## New Files

- `migrations/0011_observation_pruning.sql` — prune/tombstone projection fields.
- `crates/aver-core/src/runtime_adapters.rs` — runtime adapter boundary stubs.
- `crates/aver-core/tests/observational_memory.rs` — core acceptance tests.
- `crates/aver-cli/tests/observational_memory_cli.rs` — CLI acceptance tests.
- `crates/aver-server/tests/observational_memory_tools.rs` — server tool acceptance tests.
- `doc/runtime-adapters.md` — adapter contract documentation.

## Acceptance Criteria

- Coverage reports covered/uncovered event ids and counts.
- Compaction summaries warn on uncovered gaps.
- Checked compaction/pruning blocks while uncovered gaps remain.
- Catch-up drafts/observer flow can close gaps before summary.
- Pruning appends tombstones and never deletes observation rows/log history.
- Ordinary observation list/summary/recall hide pruned observations.
- Explicit audit list/recall preserves pruned observations.
- Replay reconstructs observation and prune state from JSONL.
- Trigger decisions include `UncoveredObservationGap`.
- CLI and MCP expose coverage, catch-up, summary, pruning, and audit recall.
- Runtime adapter boundaries are documented/stubbed for all requested agents.
- README/docs updated; ADRs untouched.
- fmt, clippy, and workspace tests pass.

## Risks

- Migration prefix must remain contiguous; verify current latest before creating `0011`.
- Existing `INSERT OR REPLACE` can erase audit semantics; replace carefully.
- Prune simulation must avoid creating active coverage gaps.
- MCP schema changes may affect clients; keep backward-compatible fields where possible.
- Replay ordering must handle duplicate global/per-agent logs idempotently.

